*\n\n*   **iPhone 16 Series (iPhone 16, 16 Plus, 16 Pro, 16 Pro Max):** Expected in September. As always, these will be major releases. Rumored features:\n    *   Faster processors (likely A18 Bionic).\n    *   Camera improvements, especially for the Pro models.\n    *   Potentially a new \"Capture Button\".\n    *   Display improvements (brighter, more efficient).\n*   **New Apple Watch:** Expected to be announced in September, with potential health and fitness improvements.\n\n**OnePlus:**\n\n*   **OnePlus 13:** The successor to the OnePlus 12. Details are scarce, but expect a late 2024 or early 2025 release with the latest Snapdragon chip.\n\n**Xiaomi:**\n\n*   **Xiaomi 15:** Expected towards the end of 2024.\n\n**Other Brands (General Expectations):**\n\n*   **Motorola:** Motorola continues to release interesting phones, particularly in the foldable and mid-range categories. Keep an eye out for updates to their Razr foldable line and new Moto G series phones.\n*   **Nothing Phone (3):** Expected mid-2024, building on their unique design language.\n*   **Oppo/Vivo/Realme:** These brands are constantly innovating, especially in camera technology and fast charging. Expect new models throughout the year with a focus on these areas.\n\n**How to Stay Updated:**\n\n*   **Tech News Websites:** Follow reputable tech news sites and blogs (e.g., The Verge, GSMArena, Android Authority, 9to5Google, MacRumors).\n*   **YouTube Channels:** Subscribe to tech review channels that cover leaks and rumors (e.g., Mrwhosetheboss, Marques Brownlee (MKBHD)).\n*   **Social Media:** Follow tech journalists and leakers on Twitter (X).\n\nTo give you more specific and helpful recommendations, tell me:\n\n*   **What is your budget?**\n*   **What features are most important to you (camera, battery life, performance, screen size, etc.)?**\n*   **Are you interested in a specific brand?**\n*   **What country are you in?** (This affects availability).\n\n",
